---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import "../../styles/globals.css";
import { Header } from "../../components/Header";
import InnerPageCTA from "../../components/InnerPageCTA.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";

const b = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout
  title="November Product Innovations - parcelLab Promise - parcelLab"
  description="parcelLab Promise empowers retailers to self-configure and display delivery promise dates. Plus updates to Customer Service Portal, Campaign Manager, and Returns Portal."
>
  <Header client:load />
  <main>
    <!-- Article Header -->
    <section class="section-generous">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-[1440px] px-6 md:px-12">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-[800px]">
          <a href={`${b}/blog/`} class="group mb-8 inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--ink-muted)] transition-colors hover:text-[#3D3AD3]">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="transition-transform group-hover:-translate-x-0.5"><path d="M19 12H5"/><path d="m12 19-7-7 7-7"/></svg>
            Back to blog
          </a>
          <span class="mb-4 inline-block rounded-full bg-[#3D3AD3]/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-[#3D3AD3]">Product Updates</span>
          <h1 class="text-display text-[var(--ink)]">November Product Innovations -- parcelLab Promise</h1>
          <div class="mt-6 flex items-center gap-4 text-sm text-[var(--ink-muted)]">
            <span>By <strong class="font-medium text-[var(--ink-secondary)]">Tinka Carrick</strong></span>
            <span class="h-1 w-1 rounded-full bg-[var(--ink-muted)]"></span>
            <time datetime="2023-12-08">December 8, 2023</time>
            <span class="h-1 w-1 rounded-full bg-[var(--ink-muted)]"></span>
            <span>7 min read</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Article Body -->
    <section class="pb-16 md:pb-24">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-[800px] px-6 md:px-12">
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed text-lg">
          Peak season is in full swing with Cyber Week showing positive numbers. Salesforce recently revealed their 2023 Cyber Week numbers which showed that global sales were up 6% year over year. With ecommerce sales growing faster than in-store retail, parcelLab has some exciting new innovations and enhancements.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">parcelLab Promise</h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          68% of consumers expect to see an estimated delivery date, yet 41% of retailers do not show a delivery date on their product detail page or only show shipping speed. parcelLab Promise empowers retailers to self-configure, adjust, and display delivery promise dates that help shoppers make faster and more confident purchase decisions.
        </p>

        <div class="my-10 rounded-2xl bg-[var(--surface-sunken)] p-8">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.1em] text-[var(--ink-muted)]">Results</p>
          <div class="mt-4 grid grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <div>
              <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#3D3AD3]">3%</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-[var(--ink-muted)]">Higher desktop conversion</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#3D3AD3]">2.1%</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-[var(--ink-muted)]">Higher mobile conversion</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#3D3AD3]">15%</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-[var(--ink-muted)]">Faster mobile checkout</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#3D3AD3]">4%</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-[var(--ink-muted)]">Less time on PDP before buying</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">Customer Service Portal</h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          The customer service portal was updated with a new option to mark tracking records as claimed, saving a timestamp and claims reason for later export to simplify claims processing.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">Campaign Manager</h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          Campaign Manager users can now define specific email messages where campaign banners are displayed, providing enhanced personalization when setting up email campaigns. If users select specific message types, the campaign builder displays banners only in those designated messages.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">Returns Portal</h2>

        <div class="mt-6 space-y-6">
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--line)] bg-[var(--surface-raised)] p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--ink)]">Google Wallet Integration</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
              Android users can now easily manage return QR codes from the returns portal in their Google Wallet, enabling customers to store and manage QR codes natively. This complements the Apple Wallet QR code feature added in September.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--line)] bg-[var(--surface-raised)] p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--ink)]">Global Returns Portal Selection</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
              Retailers with multiple Returns Portals catering to different languages can now configure a global login page for a smoother experience, simplifying the implementation of displaying multiple portals on websites.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">Additional November Improvements</h2>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="mt-1.5 h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-[#3D3AD3]"></span>
            <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]">New parcelLab portal includes a help center link, direct ticket submission capability, and a cookie banner on the login page</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="mt-1.5 h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-[#3D3AD3]"></span>
            <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]">Retailers can now set return fees per carrier that are automatically deducted in Shopify once a return is created</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="mt-1.5 h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-[#3D3AD3]"></span>
            <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]">Gift card options as alternatives to refunds for Shopify users</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="mt-1.5 h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-[#3D3AD3]"></span>
            <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]">Distance display to next Happy Returns drop-off location</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="mt-1.5 h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-[#3D3AD3]"></span>
            <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]">Parcel locker codes on returns confirmation pages</span>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <div class="my-12 border-t border-[var(--line)]"></div>

        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          All new features are now available, with availability varying based on which parcelLab products you use. Contact your account manager to learn more or log into the parcelLab Portal.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <InnerPageCTA />
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
